level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="738" level="6" match="0" type="text/javascript" value_z1z="">
et=1474641394;
function f0(d){return ld[d.getUTCDay()]+', '+lm[d.getUTCMonth()]+' '+d.getUTCDate()+', '+d.getUTCFullYear()+' at '+((d.getUTCHours()+11)%12+1)+':'+p2(d.getUTCMinutes())+':'+p2(d.getUTCSeconds())+' '+_ap(d);}
function f1(d){return ld[d.getUTCDay()]+', '+lm[d.getUTCMonth()]+' '+d.getUTCDate()+', '+d.getUTCFullYear()+' at '+p2(d.getUTCHours())+':'+p2(d.getUTCMinutes())+':'+p2(d.getUTCSeconds());}
function f2(d){return ((d.getUTCHours()+11)%12+1)+':'+p2(d.getUTCMinutes());}
function f3(d){return ''+p2(d.getUTCSeconds());}
function f4(d){return ''+_ap(d);}
function f5(d){return ld[d.getUTCDay()];}
function f6(d){return sm[d.getUTCMonth()]+' '+d.getUTCDate()+', '+d.getUTCFullYear();}
function f7(d){return ''+sm[d.getUTCMonth()];}
function f8(d){return ''+d.getUTCFullYear();}
function f9(d){return ''+d.getUTCDate();}
function f10(d){return sd1[d.getUTCDay()];}
cks={clk_hm:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f2},ij0:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f3},clk_am:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f4},ij1:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f5},ij2:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f6},cal_m:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f7},cal_y:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f8},cal_d:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f9},cal_w:{t:[{o:-14400,a:"&lt;a href=\"/time/zones/edt\" title=\"Eastern Daylight Time\"&gt;EDT&lt;/a&gt;",d:1}],f:f10}};
lm=[];lm[8]='September';sm=[];sm[8]='Sep';ld=[];ld[3]='Wednesday';ld[4]='Thursday';ld[5]='Friday';ld[6]='Saturday';sd1=['Sun','Mon','Tue','Wed','Thu','Fri','Sat'];
function _ap(d){var t=Math.floor(d.getTime()/1E3+8640000000)%86400;if(t===0){return 'Midnight';}if(t==43200){return 'Noon';}if(t&lt;43200){return 'AM';}return 'PM';}
 


</script></div></div>
</div>

level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

href="/newsletter/issue62.html" id_diff_z1z="684" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Equinox on September 22, 2016</a></h3><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="685" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="em ">Day and night will be <em hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="686" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">almost</em> equal in most places around the world on Thursday, September 22, 2016 as the Sun crosses the celestial equator and starts moving south in the sky.</p><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="687" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="653" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time. hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="652" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="653" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time. 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="670" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="672" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" value_z1z="em ">Day and night will be <em hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="685" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">almost</em> equal in most places around the world on Thursday, September 22, hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="639" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Thursday, September 22, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="640" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a a ">Equinox means "equal night," but day and night are <a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/astronomy/equinox-not-equal.html" id_diff_z1z="641" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">not exactly 12 hours each</a> on the equinoxes, only nearly. <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="642" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="652" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="653" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="673" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" 23</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="639" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Thursday, September 22, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="640" level="13" id_diff_z1z="653" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="673" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" 2016 as the Sun crosses the celestial equator and starts moving south in the sky.</p><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="687" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

class="img-tag" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="647" level="15" match="0" value_z1z="span span "><span class="img-day" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="648" level="16" match="0" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="652" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="653" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.
 <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="655" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="670" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="672" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" value_z1z="em ">Day and night will be <em hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="685" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">almost</em> equal in most places around the world on Thursday, September 22, 2016 as the Sun crosses the celestial equator and starts moving south in the sky.</p><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="686" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" <h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="637" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="638" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">September Equinox on Thursday 22 / Friday 23</a></h4>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="636" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="637" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">September Equinox on Thursday 22 / Friday 23</a></h4>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="638" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">September Equinox on Thursday 22 / Friday 23</a>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="637" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">September Equinox on Thursday 22 / Friday 23</a>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="639" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Thursday, September 22, 2016</p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="638" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Thursday, September 22, 2016</p>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="640" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a a ">Equinox means "equal night," but day and night are <a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/astronomy/equinox-not-equal.html" id_diff_z1z="641" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">not exactly 12 hours each</a> on the equinoxes, only nearly. <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="642" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="639" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a a ">Equinox means "equal night," but day and night are <a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/astronomy/equinox-not-equal.html" id_diff_z1z="640" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">not exactly 12 hours each</a> on the equinoxes, only nearly. <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/calendar/september-equinox.html" id_diff_z1z="641" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/astronomy/equinox-not-equal.html" id_diff_z1z="641" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">not exactly 12 hours each</a>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/astronomy/equinox-not-equal.html" id_diff_z1z="640" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">not exactly 12 hours each</a>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

~~~~~~~~~~~~

The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.

<div class="rd-inner" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="644" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="div h4 p p "><div class="post-img" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="645" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="646" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="span img "><span class="img-tag" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="647" level="15" match="0" value_z1z="span span "><span class="img-day" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="648" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">21</span><span class="img-month" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="649" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">SEP</span></span><img alt="Illustration image" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" height="126" id_diff_z1z="650" level="15" match="0" src="//c.tadst.com/gfx/190x126/int-day-of-peacej.jpg?1" value_z1z="" width="190"/></a></div><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="651" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="652" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="653" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.
 <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="655" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div>

<h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="652" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="653" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="651" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="652" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a></h4>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="653" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="652" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">International Day of Peace</a>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="653" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Wednesday, September 21, 2016</p>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="655" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.
 <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="656" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="654" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">The United Nations' (UN) International Day of Peace is celebrated on September 21 each year to recognize the efforts of those who have worked hard to end conflict and promote peace. The International Day of Peace is also a day of ceasefire – personal or political.
 <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/holidays/un/international-peace-day" id_diff_z1z="655" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
;

Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="673" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="674" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a class="subpage-link" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/" id_diff_z1z="675" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="strong ">Go to <strong hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="676" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Time Zone News</strong></a></div></article></li>

<li class="tab rd-btm" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id="feat2" id_diff_z1z="659" level="10" match="0" style="display:none" value_z1z="article "><article hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="660" level="11" match="0" value_z1z="div div "><div class="rd-inner" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="661" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="div h4 p p "><div class="post-img" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="662" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="663" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="span img "><span class="img-tag" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="664" level="15" match="0" value_z1z="span span "><span class="img-day" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="665" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">06</span><span class="img-month" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="666" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">NOV</span></span><img alt="Illustration image" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" height="126" id_diff_z1z="667" level="15" match="0" src="//c.tadst.com/gfx/190x126/tzmap-namerica.png?1" value_z1z="" width="190"/></a></div><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="668" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="669" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="670" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="672" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="673" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a class="subpage-link" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/" id_diff_z1z="674" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="strong ">Go to <strong hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="675" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Time Zone News</strong></a></div></article></li>

<article hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="661" level="11" match="0" value_z1z="div div "><div class="rd-inner" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="662" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="div h4 p p "><div class="post-img" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="663" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="664" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="span img "><span class="img-tag" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="665" level="15" match="0" value_z1z="span span "><span class="img-day" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="666" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">06</span><span class="img-month" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="667" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">NOV</span></span><img alt="Illustration image" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" height="126" id_diff_z1z="668" level="15" match="0" src="//c.tadst.com/gfx/190x126/tzmap-namerica.png?1" value_z1z="" width="190"/></a></div><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="669" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="670" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="673" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="674" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a class="subpage-link" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/" id_diff_z1z="675" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="strong ">Go to <strong hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="676" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Time Zone News</strong></a></div></article>

<article hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="660" level="11" match="0" value_z1z="div div "><div class="rd-inner" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="661" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="div h4 p p "><div class="post-img" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="662" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="663" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="span img "><span class="img-tag" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="664" level="15" match="0" value_z1z="span span "><span class="img-day" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="665" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">06</span><span class="img-month" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="666" level="16" match="0" value_z1z="">NOV</span></span><img alt="Illustration image" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" height="126" id_diff_z1z="667" level="15" match="0" src="//c.tadst.com/gfx/190x126/tzmap-namerica.png?1" value_z1z="" width="190"/></a></div><h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="668" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="669" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a></h4><p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="670" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p><p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="672" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p></div><div class="box-bottom tr" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="673" level="12" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a class="subpage-link" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/" id_diff_z1z="674" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="strong ">Go to <strong hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="675" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Time Zone News</strong></a></div></article>

~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<h4 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="668" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="669" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a></h4>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="670" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="669" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">USA &amp; Canada End DST Sunday, Nov 1</a>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p class="date" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="670" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="">Sunday, November 6, 2016</p>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="672" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="673" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="671" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a ">Daylight Saving Time (DST) ends and clocks are set back one hour in most of the US, Canada, and Mexico's northern border cities on Sunday, November 6, 2016, at 02:00 (2 am) local time.  <a class="read-more nw" hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/news/time/usa-canada-end-dst-2016.html" id_diff_z1z="672" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Full Story</a></p>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

~~~~~~~~~~~~

<h3 hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="682" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="a "><a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/newsletter/issue62.html" id_diff_z1z="683" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Equinox on September 22, 2016</a></h3>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/newsletter/issue62.html" id_diff_z1z="684" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Equinox on September 22, 2016</a>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<a hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" href="/newsletter/issue62.html" id_diff_z1z="683" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">Equinox on September 22, 2016</a>
;
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="685" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="em ">Day and night will be <em hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="686" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">almost</em> equal in most places around the world on Thursday, September 22, 2016 as the Sun crosses the celestial equator and starts moving south in the sky.</p>
~~~~~~~~~~~~ 
<p hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="684" level="13" match="0" value_z1z="em ">Day and night will be <em hasDiffAttrs="1" hash="0" id_diff_z1z="685" level="14" match="0" value_z1z="">almost</em> equal in most places around the world on Thursday, September 22, 2016 as the Sun crosses the celestial equator and starts moving south in the sky.</p>
;
